title: HP M6-1158ca power button light stays on for a second
message:
Hi,
I have a Compel LA-8711P board that gets power for an S5, S4, S3 and even turns on briefly with a quater fan spin, but shuts down after a second. There was a tiny amount of liquid damage around the mosfet Q43 and a 200k resistor R181. I was able to clean the corrosion off and replace R181, but still having the same issue? Any suggestions would be much appreciated, Here is a link to the schematic [URL="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B2UNwNtr3dVnVzV4NzZjbDlDSlE/view?usp=sharing"]https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B2U...ew?usp=sharing[/URL]

message: is 3V_PCH present?? What is the voltage on pins 2 and 5 from Q43??
